'''貴州小春蟲'''（[[學名|學名]]：''Vernanimalcula guizhouena''）是一種[[化石|化石]]，相信是最為古老的[[兩側對稱動物|兩側對稱動物]]。它們出土於6億至5.8億年前的[[地層|地層]]，只有0.1-0.2毫米闊。由於它們生存於{{le|馬林諾冰期|Marinoan glaciation}}末期，故被命名為小春蟲。

貴州小春蟲的化石是在[[中國|中國]][[贵州省|贵州省]][[瓮安县|瓮安县]][[陡山沱組|陡山沱組]]地层被發現。[[陡山沱組|陡山沱組]]地层完好地保存了化石，包括身體的軟體部份及細緻地方。小春蟲是三胚口結構的，有體腔、分隔的[[食道|食道]]、口器、[[肛門|肛門]]、及成對的坑，相信是藏有[[感覺器官|感覺器官]]的。

小春蟲的描述充滿爭議。一些學者指它們並非[[生物|生物]]，其實是長有[[磷酸鹽|磷酸鹽]]的埋葬人工製品。<ref name=Bengtson2004>{{cite journal en|author=Bengtson, S.|coauthors=Budd, G.|year=2004|title=Comment on "Small bilaterian fossils from 40 to 55 million years before the Cambrian"|journal=Science|volume=306|pages=1291a|doi=10.1126/science.1101338|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/sci;306/5700/1291a|accessdate=2007-06-27|pmid=15550644|issue=5700|archive-date=2008-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080216161711/http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/sci;306/5700/1291a|dead-url=no}}</ref>

貴州小春蟲的發現有重要的意義。[[動物|動物]]可能是在較為大型的體型下[[演化|演化]]成不同的[[門|門]]。[[寒武紀大爆發|寒武紀大爆發]]可能只是生物在體型上的增加及發展出能化石化的身體部份的時期。<ref>{{Cite journal en|author=Chen, J. Y., D. J. Bottjer, P. Oliveri, S. Q. Dornbos, F. Gao, S. Ruffins, H. Chi, C. W. Li, and E. H. Davidson|year=2004|title=Small bilaterian fossils from 40 to 55 million years before the cambrian|journal=Science|volume=305|pages=218-22|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/1099213v1|accessdate=2007-06-20|archive-date=2007-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001091139/http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/1099213v1|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/data/1099213/DC1/1|title=Supporting Online Material from ''Science'' magazine|accessdate=2005-10-17|archive-date=2007-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930204845/http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/data/1099213/DC1/1|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.astrobio.net/news/article1005.html|title=Article on ''Vernanimalcula'' in ''Astrobiology Magazine''|accessdate=2005-10-15|archive-date=2004-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040818163435/http://www.astrobio.net/news/article1005.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000C4E87-7070-10BF-B07083414B7F0000&sc=I100322|title=Article on ''Vernanimalcula'' in ''Scientific American''|accessdate=2005-10-15|archive-date=2007-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071010051523/http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000C4E87-7070-10BF-B07083414B7F0000&sc=I100322|dead-url=no}}</ref>

